**//SOLUTION found by nmvr2600:**

Add `@default` annotation to your class from the package: `import javax.enterprise.inject.Default;`
```
import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;
import javax.enterprise.inject.Default;

@Default
@RequestScoped
@PersistenceUnitExtension
@Slf4j
public class CustomTenantResolver implements TenantResolver {
...
```

### Expected behavior

No error message on startup.

### Actual behavior

I get the no instance of tenantResolver was found exception.

